v>\n<div class="amazingcarousel-title">Sky</div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"><a href="https://www.wonderplugin.com/imagegallery/Wild.jpg" title="Wild" data-thumbnail="https://www.wonderplugin.com/imagegallery/Wild-thumb.jpg" class="wondercarousellightbox wondercarousellightbox-55" data-group="wondercarousellightbox-55" data-mediatype=0><img src="https://www.wonderplugin.com/imagegallery/Wild.jpg" alt="Wild" data-description="" /></a></div>\n<div class="amazingcarousel-title">Wild</div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"><a href="https://www.wonderplugin.com/imagegallery/Zebra.jpg" title="Zebra" data-thumbnail="https://www.wonderplugin.com/imagegallery/Zebra-thumb.jpg" class="wondercarousellightbox wondercarousellightbox-55" data-group="wondercarousellightbox-55" data-mediatype=0><img src="https://www.wonderplugin.com/imagegallery/Zebra.jpg" alt="Zebra" data-description="" /></a></div>\n<div class="amazingcarousel-title">Zebra</div></div></li></ul><div class="amazingcarousel-prev"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-nav"></div></div></div>\n<p style="margin-top:36px;">\n<p><strong id="step4">Step 4 - Use list.xml file to define extra title and description information</strong></p>\n<p>You can use an xml file to define extra information, for example, title and description, for the images and videos in the folder.</p>\n<p>The name of the xml file must be <code>list.xml</code> and it must be placed inside the folder.</p>\n<p>For example, the following xml file adds extra information for two items in the carousel.</p>\n<p>The first item <code>myimage.jpg</code> defines title and description for the image <code>myimage.jpg</code>.</p>\n<p>The second item <code>myvideo-poster.jpg</code> defines title and description for the video <code>myvideo.mp4</code>, because the image <code>myvideo-poster.jpg</code> is the poster image of this video.</p>\n<p>Please note, you need to use xml key <code>image</code> to add extra information to an image/video in the folder, and the filename must match.</p>\n<pre class="brush: xml; title: ; notranslate">\r\n&lt;list&gt;\r\n  &lt;item&gt;\r\n    &lt;image&gt;myimage.jpg&lt;/image&gt;\r\n    &lt;title&gt;Image Title&lt;/title&gt;\r\n    &lt;description&gt;Denique liberavisse cu duo, no mea iusto rationibus. At pro choro feugait epicuri, vero ponderum patrioque mel ei.&lt;/description&gt;\r\n  &lt;/item&gt;\r\n  &lt;item&gt;\r\n    &lt;image&gt;myvideo-poster.jpg&lt;/image&gt;\r\n    &lt;title&gt;Video Title&lt;/title&gt;\r\n    &lt;description&gt;Denique liberavisse cu duo, no mea iusto rationibus. At pro choro feugait epicuri, vero ponderum patrioque mel ei.&lt;/description&gt;\r\n  &lt;/item&gt;\r\n&lt;/list&gt;\r\n</pre>\n<p><strong id="step5">Step 5 - Use list.xml file to add YouTube and Vimeo videos</strong></p>\n<p>You can also use the list.xml file to add YouTube and Vimeo videos to the carousel.</p>\n<p>For example, the following xml content add one YouTube video and one Vimeo video to the carousel. The type of a Youtube video is 2, the type of a Vimeo video is 3.</p>\n<pre class="brush: xml; title: ; notranslate">\r\n&lt;list&gt;\r\n  &lt;item&gt;\r\n    &lt;type&gt;2&lt;/type&gt;\r\n    &lt;image&gt;https://img.youtube.com/vi/wswxQ3mhwqQ/0.jpg&lt;/image&gt;\r\n    &lt;video&gt;https://www.youtube.com/embed/wswxQ3mhwqQ&lt;/video&gt;\r\n    &lt;title&gt;YouTube&lt;/title&gt;\r\n    &lt;description&gt;WonderPlugin Carousel&lt;/description&gt;\r\n  &lt;/item&gt;\r\n  &lt;item&gt;\r\n    &lt;type&gt;3&lt;/type&gt;\r\n    &lt;image&gt;https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/545650849_640.jpg&lt;/image&gt;\r\n    &lt;video&gt;https://player.vimeo.com/video/147079122&lt;/video&gt;\r\n    &lt;title&gt;Vimeo&lt;/title&gt;\r\n    &lt;description&gt;WonderPlugin Carousel&lt;/description&gt;\r\n  &lt;/item&gt;\r\n&lt;/list&gt;\r\n</pre>\n<p id="extra" style="margin-top:48px;"><strong>Extra - Dynamically define the image import folder</strong></p>\n<p>You can also dynamically define a folder in the carousel shortcode so you can specify a different web folder on the post/page where the carousel is added.</p>\n<p>For example:</p>\n<pre class="brush: xml; title: ; notranslate">\r\n[wonderplugin_carousel id=&quot;55&quot; data-importfolder=&quot;galleries/2018&quot;]\r\n</pre>\n<p>Please note, the carousel itself must be an "Import folder" gallery, otherwise the attribute <code>data-importfolder</code> will not work. The value of <code>data-importfolder</code> should be the relative path to the WordPress root folder. If you don''t know the value of your selected folder, you can goto the plugin, select the folder in the "Import Folder" dialog, and copy the value of the "Selected folder".</p>\n<p><a class="wplightbox" href="https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/carousel-import-folder.png"><img src="https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/carousel-import-folder.png" alt="" width="815" height="487" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-5853" srcset="https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/carousel-import-folder.png 815w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/carousel-import-folder-240x143.png 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/carousel-import-folder-600x359.png 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/carousel-import-folder-768x459.png 768w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/carousel-import-folder-75x45.png 75w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/carousel-import-folder-500x300.png 500w" sizes="(max-width: 815px) 100vw, 815px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:39:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n	